I just found this in my server lol. Can someone elaborate on its uses?

[code]    public boolean GoodDistance(int objectX, int objectY, int playerX, int playerY, int distance) {
        for (int i = 0; i <= distance; i++) {
            for (int j = 0; j <= distance; j++) {
                if ((objectX + i) == playerX
                        && ((objectY + j) == playerY || (objectY - j) == playerY
                        || objectY == playerY)) {
                    return true;
                } else if ((objectX - i) == playerX
                        && ((objectY + j) == playerY || (objectY - j) == playerY
                        || objectY == playerY)) {
                    return true;
                } else if (objectX == playerX
                        && ((objectY + j) == playerY || (objectY - j) == playerY
                        || objectY == playerY)) {
                    return true;
                }
            }
        }
        return false;
    }[/code]

isn't it a drastic over statement of this?

[code]public boolean GoodDistance(int objectX, int objectY, int playerX, int playerY, int distance) {
        return (Math.sqrt(Math.pow(playerX - objectX, 2) + Math.pow(playerY - objectY, 2)) <= distance);
    }[/code]
